comment:
* Helper class to generate and store each of the digests and prefixes * sent to the Instant App Resolver. *

* Since intent filters may want to handle multiple hosts within a * domain [eg “*.google.com”], the resolver is presented with multiple * hash prefixes. For example, "a.b.c.d.e" generates digests for * "d.e", "c.d.e", "b.c.d.e" and "a.b.c.d.e". * * @hide

variables.name: UNDEFINED
variables.comment:
* A special instance that represents and undefined digest used for cases that a host was
         * not provided or is irrelevant to the response.

variables.name: mDigestBytes
variables.comment: Full digest of the domain hashes

variables.name: mDigestPrefix
variables.comment: The first 5 bytes of the domain hashes

variables.name: mDigestPrefixSecure
variables.comment: The first 5 bytes of the domain hashes interspersed with random data

methods.name: private static byte[][] generateDigest(String hostName, int maxDigests)
public int[] getDigestPrefixSecure()
methods.comment:
* Returns a digest prefix with additional random prefixes interspersed.
         * @hide

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)

methodNames: private static byte[][] generateDigest(String hostName, int maxDigests)
